              :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-accent-900 hover:text-accent-600': activeAccordion!=id }"
              class="cursor-pointer group text-black"
            >
              <button
                @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
                class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
              >
                <span>{word4}</span>
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-600 -rotate-[45deg]"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  ><path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
                >
              </button>
              <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
                <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-accent-600">
                  {definition4}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          class="inline"
          width="20em"
          height="20em"
          viewBox="0 0 32 32"
        >
          <style>
            .word {
              font-size: 3px;
              fill: #ff7a00;
              font-family: "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            }
          </style>
          <line
            x1="1"
            y1="2"
            x2="8"
            y2="2"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-linecap="round"></line>
          <line
            x1="1"
            y1="7"
            x2="8"
            y2="7"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-linecap="round"></line>
          <line
            x1="1"
            y1="12"
            x2="5"
            y2="12"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-linecap="round"></line>
          <path
            d="M 3 15 v 11 h 18 m 8 -8 v -16 h -17"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            fill="none"
            stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <text class="word" x="12" y="7">{word1.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
          <text class="word" x="10" y="12">{word2.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
          <text class="word" x="9" y="17">{word3.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
          <text class="word" x="9" y="22">{word4.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div
        x-data="{ activeAccordion: '', setActiveAccordion(id) { this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id } }"
        class="md:col-span-2 md:w-3/4 mx-auto"
      >
        <p
          class="text-2xl tracking-tight text-center font-medium text-black mb-4"
        >
          Story
        </p>
        <div x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }" class="text-gray-500 text-left">
          <p class="mb-4">
The salty spray stung Amelia's eyes as she clung to the mast, the storm's fury a maelstrom threatening to swallow their ship whole. Lightning split the sky, momentarily illuminating the white egrets circling overhead, their beauty an unsettling contrast to the chaos below. Just moments ago, the sky had been a tranquil canvas of orange and pink, the egrets graceful dancers on the cusp of the horizon. Now, they were caught in the same desperate struggle, their wings buffeting against the relentless wind.
          </p>
          <div
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            :class="activeAccordion==id ? 'hidden' : ''"
            class="cursor-pointer text-opacity-70 underline hover:text-accent-900"
          >
            [Continue Reading]
          </div>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <p class="mb-4">
Amelia, a seasoned sailor, had witnessed many storms, but none with such an air of malice. It felt personal, a punishment for a yet-unknown transgression. A memory surfaced, sharp and indelible. Her captain, a man whose weathered face held the secrets of a thousand voyages, his eyes glinting with a perpetual mistrust. He had entrusted her with a secret mission, one shrouded in subterfuge. Now, with the wrath of the sea upon them, Amelia wondered if the captain's paranoia had been a premonition, a premonition she had foolishly dismissed.
            </p>
            <p>
The storm raged for what felt like an eternity. When the skies finally cleared, revealing a bruised but unbroken horizon, the egrets were gone. An unsettling calm had settled over the ocean, a quiet that echoed the hollowness in Amelia's heart. The captain was nowhere to be found. The storm, it seemed, had taken more than just the fair weather. It had taken a secret, leaving behind a mystery as vast and indelible as the ocean itself.  
            </p>
            <div
              @click="setActiveAccordion('')"
              :class="activeAccordion==id ? '' : 'hidden'"
              class="cursor-pointer text-opacity-70 underline hover:text-accent-900 mt-4"
            >
              [Hide]
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
